<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Compare Author's Purpose</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; padding: 20px; max-width: 800px; margin: auto; }
    h1 { color: #2c3e50; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 20px 0; }
    th, td { border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 10px; vertical-align: top; }
    th { background-color: #f8f8f8; }
    textarea { width: 100%; height: 80px; }
    .correct-answer { background-color: #e8f8e8; border: 1px dashed #2ecc71; padding: 10px; margin-top: 10px; }
    button { padding: 8px 12px; margin-top: 10px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>📘 Compare Author’s Purpose</h1>
  <p><strong>Compare</strong> <em>“Families in Many Cultures”</em> and <em>“The World Is Your Family”</em>.</p>

  <table>
    <tr>
      <th>“Families in Many Cultures”</th>
      <th>“The World Is Your Family”</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><textarea id="input1" placeholder="What is the author’s purpose?"></textarea></td>
      <td><textarea id="input2" placeholder="What is the author’s purpose?"></textarea></td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <button onclick="showAnswers()">✅ Gợi ý mục đích chính xác</button>

  <div id="answers" class="correct-answer" style="display: none;">
    <strong>✅ Gợi ý đúng:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Families in Many Cultures:</strong> to show how families in different places celebrate similar events like birthdays and holidays.</li>
      <li><strong>The World Is Your Family:</strong> to explain how people around the world are connected and part of a global family — encouraging kindness and respect.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p><em>💬 Take turns with a partner: Tell how the authors' purposes are different.</em></p>

</body>
<script>
  function showAnswers() {
    document.getElementById("answers").style.display = "block";
  }
</script>
</html>
